https://docs.spring.io/spring-framework/docs/5.2.x/spring-framework-reference/web.html#websocket

- raw WebSocket interactions
- WebSocket emulation through SockJS
- publish-subscribe messaging through STOMP as a sub-protocol

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Handshake
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
HTTP request with Upgrade command to
use open TCP connection

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
When to use
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
It is the combination of low latency, high frequency, and high volume that make
the best case for the use of WebSocket.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SockJS protocol
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fallback if Websocket is not supported

# Causes
proxies outside out control:
- are not configured to pass on the Upgrade header
- close long-lived connections that appear to be idle

Websocket is then emulated with HTTP-based techniques


